www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asean-disaster-recovery-reference-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "3f64e8d6bad0cf8fcf405ea1c4bfcc683e69c16cc30c3f39191e3701b55aa9b4"}, "3": {"node_id": "5afb9f5c-c5b4-43e2-88f7-dd0f56591af2", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asean-disaster-recovery-reference-guide", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "abd7eef79072f6f80b5cf83e9de52b1d937321f281fcbaecf923757c27faa8cd"}}, "hash": "cf1c75a67cc4709bea34c86158f14513ba687585fb153eb59eba6c8d7ce01559", "text": "a balance between the assessment of \u2018economic loss\u2019 and \u2018post disaster needs\u2019 was established. It led to the establishment of a Technical Disaster Assessment Committee led by the MPI, the development of a Manual for Damage and Loss Calculation and further training for officials from key line ministries.59 The methodology was also adapted to the provincial level. In khammouane province of Lao PDR, the damage, loss, and needs assessment system was further strengthened through the development of province-specific tools. These included the Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for Damage, Loss and Needs Assessment and Guidelines on Planning, Budgeting, and Financing for post disaster recovery and reconstruction activities. The SOPs include guidance on the purpose, timing, scope and funding for the assessment as well as pre-assessment activities and procedures for conducting assessments.60 Despite the challenges of baseline information and better data, the PDNA process in Lao PDR has been integrated with recovery and planning. The PDNA is seen as a useful tool for resource mobilization particularly with development partners interested in supporting specific components of recovery and reconstruction. 59 The Wor